==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Papacy
<hw>Pa"pa*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>papatia</ets>, fr. L. <ets>papa</ets> a father, bishop. See
<er>Pope</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office and dignity of the
pope, or pontiff, of Rome; papal jurisdiction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The popes, collectively; the succession of
popes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The Roman Catholic religion; -- commonly used by the
opponents of the Roman Catholics in disparagement or in an opprobrious
sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Papagay</ent>⟦br⟧
